<dl id="n36060j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36060j">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36060j"> 60(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> glibb</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Until about the beginning of the eighteenth century the Irish wore the <mark><i>glibb</i> or long flowing hair</mark>, and also the crombeal or beard on the upper lip. <small> James Hardiman, <a name="JHHT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JHHT"><cite title="source">The History of the Town and County of the Town of Galway</cite></a> (1820, rpt. 1926) 202n</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
